  "text": "The concept of social support included emotional, instrumental, and informational subcategories. Each dimension of support was measured using a 4-item, 5-point Likert scale. Therefore, total scores of social support ranged from 0 to 48, with higher scores indicating better social support. A previous study examined the validity and reliability of the social support scale [CITATION_1] . The social support scale has been applied in previous studies of immigrant and native-born women [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The internal consistency of the scale in this study was assessed using Cronbach's alpha and was 0.944 (0.957 for immigrant women and 0.927 for native-born women).",
